The paper deals with propositional dynamic logic, which is a logical system used to reason about programs and their behavior. This makes it likely to belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses program equivalence, which is a topic in programming languages and semantics, making the Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category another likely choice. The paper also deals with undecidability, which is a topic in computational complexity theory, making the Computational Complexity (cs.CC) sub-category a possible fit. The paper also mentions the use of models, which is a topic in Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), and the Stanford Encyclopedia of Philosophy, which suggests a connection to Software Engineering (cs.SE).
